{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Good morning everybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3000,"text":"I work with really amazing,"},{"time":5000,"text":"little, itty-bitty creatures called cells."},{"time":8000,"text":"And let me tell you what it's like"},{"time":10000,"text":"to grow these cells in the lab."},{"time":12000,"text":"I work in a lab where we take cells out of their native environment."},{"time":15000,"text":"We plate them into dishes"},{"time":17000,"text":"that we sometimes call petri dishes."},{"time":19000,"text":"And we feed them -- sterilely of course --"},{"time":22000,"text":"with what we call cell culture media -- which is like their food --"},{"time":25000,"text":"and we grow them in incubators."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28000,"text":"Why do I do this?"},{"time":30000,"text":"We observe the cells in a plate,"},{"time":32000,"text":"and they're just on the surface."},{"time":34000,"text":"But what we're really trying to do in my lab"},{"time":37000,"text":"is to engineer tissues out of them."},{"time":40000,"text":"What does that even mean?"},{"time":42000,"text":"Well it means growing an actual heart,"},{"time":44000,"text":"let's say,"},{"time":46000,"text":"or grow a piece of bone"},{"time":48000,"text":"that can be put into the body."},{"time":50000,"text":"Not only that, but they can also be used for disease models."},{"time":53000,"text":"And for this purpose, traditional cell culture techniques"},{"time":55000,"text":"just really aren't enough."},{"time":57000,"text":"The cells are kind of homesick;"},{"time":59000,"text":"the dish doesn't feel like their home."},{"time":61000,"text":"And so we need to do better at copying their natural environment"},{"time":63000,"text":"to get them to thrive."},{"time":65000,"text":"We call this the biomimetic paradigm --"},{"time":67000,"text":"copying nature in the lab."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70000,"text":"Let's take the example of the heart,"},{"time":72000,"text":"the topic of a lot of my research."},{"time":74000,"text":"What makes the heart unique?"},{"time":76000,"text":"Well, the heart beats,"},{"time":78000,"text":"rhythmically, tirelessly, faithfully."},{"time":81000,"text":"We copy this in the lab"},{"time":83000,"text":"by outfitting cell culture systems with electrodes."},{"time":86000,"text":"These electrodes act like mini pacemakers"},{"time":88000,"text":"to get the cells to contract in the lab."},{"time":91000,"text":"What else do we know about the heart?"},{"time":93000,"text":"Well, heart cells are pretty greedy."},{"time":95000,"text":"Nature feeds the heart cells in your body"},{"time":97000,"text":"with a very, very dense blood supply."},{"time":99000,"text":"In the lab, we micro-pattern channels"},{"time":101000,"text":"in the biomaterials"},{"time":103000,"text":"on which we grow the cells,"},{"time":105000,"text":"and this allows us to flow the cell culture media, the cells' food,"},{"time":108000,"text":"through the scaffolds where we're growing the cells --"},{"time":111000,"text":"a lot like what you might expect"},{"time":113000,"text":"from a capillary bed in the heart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"So this brings me to lesson number one:"},{"time":118000,"text":"life can do a lot with very little."},{"time":121000,"text":"Let's take the example of electrical stimulation."},{"time":123000,"text":"Let's see how powerful just one of these essentials can be."},{"time":127000,"text":"On the left, we see a tiny piece of beating heart tissue"},{"time":130000,"text":"that I engineered from rat cells in the lab."},{"time":132000,"text":"It's about the size of a mini marshmallow."},{"time":134000,"text":"And after one week, it's beating."},{"time":136000,"text":"You can see it in the upper left-hand corner."},{"time":138000,"text":"But don't worry if you can't see it so well."},{"time":140000,"text":"It's amazing that these cells beat at all."},{"time":143000,"text":"But what's really amazing"},{"time":145000,"text":"is that the cells, when we electrically stimulate them,"},{"time":147000,"text":"like with a pacemaker,"},{"time":149000,"text":"that they beat so much more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151000,"text":"But that brings me to lesson number two:"},{"time":153000,"text":"cells do all the work."},{"time":155000,"text":"In a sense, tissue engineers have a bit of an identity crisis here,"},{"time":158000,"text":"because structural engineers"},{"time":160000,"text":"build bridges and big things,"},{"time":163000,"text":"computer engineers, computers,"},{"time":165000,"text":"but what we are doing"},{"time":167000,"text":"is actually building enabling technologies for the cells themselves."},{"time":170000,"text":"What does this mean for us?"},{"time":172000,"text":"Let's do something really simple."},{"time":174000,"text":"Let's remind ourselves"},{"time":176000,"text":"that cells are not an abstract concept."},{"time":179000,"text":"Let's remember that our cells sustain our lives"},{"time":182000,"text":"in a very real way."},{"time":184000,"text":"\"We are what we eat,\" could easily be described"},{"time":187000,"text":"as, \"We are what our cells eat.\""},{"time":189000,"text":"And in the case of the flora in our gut,"},{"time":191000,"text":"these cells may not even be human."},{"time":195000,"text":"But it's also worth noting"},{"time":197000,"text":"that cells also mediate our experience of life."},{"time":200000,"text":"Behind every sound, sight, touch, taste and smell"},{"time":203000,"text":"is a corresponding set of cells"},{"time":205000,"text":"that receive this information"},{"time":207000,"text":"and interpret it for us."},{"time":209000,"text":"It begs the question:"},{"time":211000,"text":"shall we expand our sense of environmental stewardship"},{"time":214000,"text":"to include the ecosystem of our own bodies?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":217000,"text":"I invite you to talk about this with me further,"},{"time":219000,"text":"and in the meantime, I wish you luck."},{"time":222000,"text":"May none of your non-cancer cells"},{"time":224000,"text":"become endangered species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}